Don '''Andrea Santoro''' was a [[Catholic]] [[priest]] who was murdered on [[February 5]], [[2006]] at the Santa Maria Church in [[Trabzon]], [[Turkey]], where he served as a member of the Catholic church's [[Fidei donum]] [[missionary]] program. A 16-year-old high school student was arrested two days later carrying a [[9mm]] pistol. The student told [[police]] he had been influenced by the [[Jyllands-Posten Muhammad cartoons controversy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.int.iol.co.za/index.php?set_id=1&click_id=24&art_id=vn20060208033427794C349514|publisher=Independent  Online|title=Murder of priest 'religious revenge'|date=February 8, 2006}}</ref>

At Don Santoro's funeral at the [[Basilica of St. John Lateran]], [[His Eminence]], [[Camillo Cardinal Ruini]], the vicar of the Diocese of Rome, has mentioned in his homily that the possible beatification process for Don Santoro may be opened after February [[2011]].

